  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to report suspicious transactions to relevant authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n2. Identifying and reporting large cash transactions\n3. Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Training staff to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nHowever, I want to be clear that I can provide general information about this topic, but I cannot give specific legal advice.",
